snippet.textDisplay: I love you Jaclyn ALWAYS! I'm so happy you guys found each other because ur perfect together and everyone deserves love like that! In so happy u won the AIA award I voted for you every day with 4 different email accts so that I could vote more than once a day that's how much I love you. My IG handle is @princessbeautymua and I've dmed you written comments and tweeted at you. I even made a post on my IG my rarebeauty story and tagged you in it. It world seriously mean more than u could ever imagine if you would read my post( its a sideways pic of me in a pink tank top w/ pink lugz on) and my dms PLEASE PLEASE I'm begging you 🙏🙏 I'm commenting this because I desperately need a little help. In 2011 I lost my dad after having a friend watch my toddler for 1 1/2 yrs so I could move in and care for my dad full time. 5 months later I had emergency surgery and sadly was diagnosed w/ incurable cancer. I given 2 yrs to live by cancer specialists. Down the rabbit hole I went. Long, hard and fast into a deep dark abyss. I was plagued with anxiety of waiting for the other shoe to drop, (ALWAYS going to bed wondering if I'd wake up) as well as depression and despair. In 2004 my dreams of becoming a healer and a beauty professional came true and I was licensed as an Esthetician/MUA & Nail Tech. It was my career but also my #1 passion besides my kids and family. I love helping people see thier beauty and learn to bring it out as well as accentuate it. I also loved using my "healing hands" as my family calls them to help people take care of thier skin. Cancer stole a majority of the function and mobility in my dominant hand and arm. I have a huge hole in the bones in that arm and my hand won't do much more than stay in a ball pointed down. With that, losing my dad and my career I literally had no hope. I was so devestated. Before long I survived the expiration date given to me by Drs and decided cancer had already stole to many years of my life and I wouldn't give it more! I started practicing, relearning & training my other hand to do makeup. After that i started posting to my ig account & turned it into a Mkup acct because I want to be a voice in the disabled & makeup communities to show anyone facing a struggle similar to mine or any anxiety, depression or adversity that thier dreams are achievable and attainable. I want to encourage them and cheer them on, I want to be a light in the darkness, but more than anything I want to be a spokesperson in the disabled community showing the world we are NOT fragile and BROKEN! That disability is NOT inability. That is my goal in 2020 and especially with all the sorrow & terrible things going on in the world right now I think we need it more than ever!  Unfortunately I'm having an extremely hard time getting my voice heard. I was hoping maybe you could share my message and my IG on your channel and help me accomplish my goal. It would seriously mean more than you know. My IG is @princessbeautymua if you'd like to read some of my posts and positive messages. Thank you for your time, for reading my messages & comments.  Also for all the smiles & happiness u bring me. Any1 reading I hope ur healthy and safe I would love if ud chk my IG and help w/ my goal of getting my story out there so I can help others also PLEASE like this so Jaclyn sees it🙏🙏
